There once was a very smart but sadly blind duck. When it was still a smallduckling it was renowned for its good vision. But sadly as the duck grew olderit caught a sickness which caused its eyesight to worsen. It became so bad, thatthe duck couldn’t read the notes it once took containing much of inline mathjust like its favoured equation:
$d = u_c \cdot k$
d =uc·k
. Only displayed equations remainedlegible so it could still read
That annoyed the smart duck, as it wasn’t able to do its research any longer. Itcalled for its underduckling and said: “Go, find me the best eye ducktor thereis. He shall heal me from my disease!”
